From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: herdr maintainers <maintainers@herdr.dev>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] force system ConPTY

Herdr should use the ConPTY functions exported by kernel32.dll and must not
load a bare conpty.dll from PATH. portable-pty's sideload probe is intentional
for WezTerm's bundled OpenConsole.exe/conpty.dll pair, but Herdr does not ship
that pair.

Herdr issue: https://github.com/ogulcancelik/herdr/issues/761
Vendored base: portable-pty 0.9.0
---
 vendor/portable-pty/src/win/psuedocon.rs | 9 +--------
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/vendor/portable-pty/src/win/psuedocon.rs b/vendor/portable-pty/src/win/psuedocon.rs
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/vendor/portable-pty/src/win/psuedocon.rs
+++ b/vendor/portable-pty/src/win/psuedocon.rs
@@ -49,14 +49,7 @@ fn load_conpty() -> ConPtyFuncs {
         "this system does not support conpty.  Windows 10 October 2018 or newer is required",
     );
-
-    // We prefer to use a sideloaded conpty.dll and openconsole.exe host deployed
-    // alongside the application.  We check for this after checking for kernel
-    // support so that we don't try to proceed and do something crazy.
-    if let Ok(sideloaded) = ConPtyFuncs::open(Path::new("conpty.dll")) {
-        sideloaded
-    } else {
-        kernel
-    }
+
+    kernel
 }

 lazy_static! {
